WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.435
Your API is fast in dev. In production, under real load — is it?

2
00:00:04.435 --> 00:00:05.846
Staff-only, secured behind Django admin auth.

3
00:00:05.846 --> 00:00:15.472
One dashboard: P99 latency, error rate, DB queries, and scale signals.

4
00:00:15.472 --> 00:00:22.759
Drill into any request — headers and body, redacted and capped, opt-in only.

5
00:00:22.759 --> 00:00:28.512
api/diagnostics/nplusone/ — 76 queries per request, 68% of total DB time.

6
00:00:28.512 --> 00:00:34.746
One click on the offender → straight to root-cause correlation for it.

7
00:00:34.746 --> 00:00:45.340
CPU, RAM, Redis, Postgres — every tier, hover for the exact percentage.

8
00:00:45.340 --> 00:00:48.732
WebSocket lifecycle and raw event logs, same level of detail.

9
00:00:48.732 --> 00:00:57.817
Generate a bottleneck report — ranked P1/P2/P3 findings.

10
00:00:57.817 --> 00:01:04.475
Rendered PDF, ready to download.

11
00:01:04.475 --> 00:01:07.538
Downloaded.

12
00:01:07.538 --> 00:01:09.640
django-perfy — pip install "django-perfy[reports]"
